76561197975821970,Not Recommended,304730,29205972,Posted: 12 January,all,aramcgregor,"I had high hopes for Train Fever, at first glance it has everything you could want from a new Transport Tycoon/Railroad Tycoon game: Nice graphics, plenty of vehicles, growing cities and industry.Visually Train Fever is nice. I have had some frame rate issues with every computer I have ran it on (including my new PC, which can run Just Cause 3 and Fallout on max settings), but the game remained playable from that perspective.The economic side of the game is the first big let down. There are far too few industries and given it takes time and patients to get them even remotely profitable, there really isn't much incentive to bother.What really kills the game for me though, is the track building and routing. It is incredibly tricky to build a bridge over a road for instance. To get double track working properly is also much much harder than it should be.To be fair, the developer had released several updates (including to the interace and trackbuilding) but none have made the game worth playing for me. The time spent on their free (cosmetic) update- the American scenery was appreciated, but would have been much better spent on the gameplay.The release of Transport Fever rubbed salt into the wound: improvements that should have been made to Train Fever were implemented there instead. It would have been nice if the developer had put the Train related improvements into Train Fever as a gesture of good will.To put things into perspective, Railroad Tycoon 3 is a comparitavely challenging business simulation with dozens of industries, a basic version of the stock market and far more interesting maps. It beats Train Fever in every aspect apart from graphics and was released back in 2003 (and work on my Windows 10 machine)."
76561198190710127,Recommended,304730,18732858,"Posted: 28 October, 2015",all,aubergine18,"Changing my review to a tentitive thumbs up. Some tips so you don't hate it as much as I did when I first started playing...There are quite a few clunky things about this game, and it's one of those where you end up restarting quite a few times until you work out the basics, but after the frustrations there's a pretty decent game waiting to be found.Enable the ""No main lines"" mod that comes with the game (Advanced tab when starting game) and suddenly it becomes a whole lot more enjoyable (although you can't get achievements with the mod enabled, which means you can't unlock the later start years - just leave an empty map running overnight without the mod to get round that).You can group stops (eg. tram station and train station) so that people will treat them as a single destination - this makes a huge difference to how they travel, because they'll more readily use mixed transport types to get to their destination."
