,Recommended,304730,28727091,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,Pvt Puddles,"This is a very excellent game, I really enjoy it.  I love watching my empire sprawl across the map, never to be tamed.Unfortunately, there are a few gamebreaking issues.  The game is called Train Fever, though the best use of your resources is with trucks delivering cargo.  Busses are cool and work in conjunction with trains well, but they bring in very little profit, if done right.  Cargo trains can bring in loads of profit, but are unstable.  It is hard to balance the correct number of cars and how much the factory produces.  Long distance cargo runs are not profitable.  The train maintanane cost outweighs the profits, or the factory/factories will not produce enough to make a train worthwhile.  Often times, neither factory on the lin e will increase, even though both are getting all their goods shipped in a timely manner, resulting in profit loss as the train gets older and becomes obsolite.  Trucks work better, with very tiny maintanance costs, and can therefore better serve the cargo industry.Passanger trains are another matter.  Connecting 2 nearby cities with a single train works well and is very profitable early on, but this is train fever.  That means we want to see some trains running around.  So you improve your tracks, and have 4 cities connected in a loop.  Guess what?  Unless you get newer, faster trains, they aren't going to make a profit.  So now it's in the 1950s, and your loop is profitable.  So let's expand, shall we?Except passengers don't want to go, which doesn't make sense.  A distant, far off city is now accesible for a short train ride, but still no one does.  I have three train lines, one is a loop of four cities.  The other two use that same loop, but also add 2+ extra cities in a bigger loop.  The first line is the most profitable, because for some reason the simulated citizens DO NOT like to go very far.  Anyway, enough ranting.Other than that, the game is very fun, and I would definately recommend.  It could use some work, but I still play it and it makes me happy.Then there is always that dude who jumps off your train mid-transit.*I got this game on sale for $3 (90% off)"
