,Recommended,304730,12220777,"Posted: 24 September, 2014",all,Pdguru,"Like many comments before, this is a game with great potential.  If you can get past the rather odd and very slow start, it's really quite fun, even in this skelton form and clunck track laying mechanics.  But it's a strange place this Tran Fever Land, not least because of ghostly, empty and too-modern looking and generic towns for 1850 and a landscape desperately lacking in flora and fauna... or life of any sort.  Or anything for that matter.  Indeed, with no 3D texture to the grass or cropfields alike, it's like a tabletop.But perhaps that's where the character of the game, today at least, comes in.  It's a nice cross between a huge model railway and a 3D animated world.  Any new game is like watching a new sitcom on TV - you have to wait to get and idea of the theme, characters and essense before you can settle in.  And you have to give it a number of hours to do that.  so BE PATIENT.  Don't switch channels to soon, folks.Once I got into the visual style and the towns grew and new vhicles came online I found myself getting quite excited to see old style cars doing the long drive in and between towns (although again the game years and vehicles some out of alignment).  Enthusiatic to get the new, bigger locomotive, combine the stations and bus stops and see passengers begin to bustle and jossle to get to the bus and train.  I even held the trains up a few times to wait for the busload of commuters whose had just pulled up.  Did I care about them?  Or did I just want their fare?  Both actually.  And that means the game is already OK - but it COULD be great.I certainly hope the makers finish the game.  With the addition of more life to the worldscape, some greater variation in the people (visually and movements), and simplification or vehicle replacement, this could truly be the next generation of Transport Tycoom Deluxe.UPDATE 4-14-15:  Well, the updates have stopped, so I guess th develpers have moved on.  A pity because with a few enhancements they could have had a really good game here.  As it is, it's an OK game and I stick with my thumbs up."
