76561198088104546,Recommended,304730,18244228,"Posted: 28 September, 2015",all,RoadHog,"This is definately no Railroad Tycoon program.It is much more simplified.In a way it isn't even a Train Simulator.  In fact you don't even have to run any trains if you don't want to.You can run a Stage Line instead and still make millions of dollars.  Of course you can run both trains and coaches.The trains are hard to operate unless your simply running pont to point.  The signaling system is too simple to be of much good if you try running multiple trains on one track.  There is only one size Train Station, BIG.  There is no small Train Station that you can place at a distant Industry. There are three different sizes of train stations but even the smallest takes up space equal to 3 city blocks. They look silly sitting next to a dinky logging camp.The industries are spread haphazardly about the map.  You might find an Oil Well but the Refinery could be halfway across the map.  It isn't cost effective to service since comodities bring very little cash compared to Passengers.  You can of course but it will take years to get a return on your investment.Cargo hauling by Horsedrawn wagons or Freight Trucks is more cost effective than trains but unlike trains they can't haul freight to an industry and then pick up the goods produced. For example a Truck delivering lumber won't automatically change and take a load of goods made from the lumber.  You have to buy a seperate truck for goods, Not very realistic.Graphics are pretty bad,  Inside towns or cities it's not bad but out on the highways and tracks it's bad.  The land is bare and boring with an occasional tree or two.  Even shades of green would be better than dirt and sand.If you use a Trackball or a wheel less mouse you will have problems scrolling some popup windows once you exceed 9 Lines.  Scrolling these windows requires a Mouse wheel.  Poor design.Now you might be wondering why I recommend this game.I'm enjoying running Stagecoaches and fine tuning the profit making.I like being able to zoom in and see my coaches moving along and looking at all the people inside towns.Cute things like watching a coach stop to let pedestrians cross the street.I'm sure to discover new things as I play along.  I'll add them here if I do.I'm having fun,  so yes I recommend it."
