,Recommended,304730,12039133,"Posted: 9 September, 2014",all,AnonOmis1000,"I would recommend this game to anyone who likes Tycoon games or OpenTTD. In my opinion this blows OpenTTD out of the water. First of all there's no grid system, so your roads and rail lines are more natural and fluid. Along with that, stations don't have an area of influence. The AI is smart enough to know that, if a station is close enough, it will take supplies and passengers there. The graphics are very good too. It looks great and I run the game on a laptop. I did have issues starting it up because it wasn't choosing the right graphics card, but it's fixed now. The audio is also great, both the sound effects and the music. The music is freaking awesome!As far as game play goes, if you've played games like this, it's pretty easy to understand.Now there are a few detractors. It isn't very well optomized for lower end machines, but that's minor as in this game skipping is only an annoyance. There also no in game tutorials, but I see that getting fixed in the future. The biggest draw back of this game is it's price. $35 for a game like this is pretty steep. I'm not too sure it's worth the price tag, so I'd recommend looking for it on sale."
,Recommended,304730,24171578,"Posted: 7 July, 2016",all,ThePCGamer101,"DISCLAIMER: This is a first impressions review, and NOT a full review, if you want a full review, then please read better reviews then minePLEASE NOTE: I recommended this game with some exceptions, overall if the game did not live up to just a tiny expectation, I would not have recommended it at all, so please read the review carefully if you are thinking of buying/playing this gameA new fever is in the works, it's called Train Fever!Not really...Train Fever is a game developed by Urban Games and published by Gambitious Digital Entertainment and it's mostly like the classic Transport Tycoon Deluxe and OpenTTD, only... it's not as goodTrain Fever is a fun game to play, although I don't know why they just called it Train Fever as you can also add buses and trams but anyway, however, the game is very clunky and sometimes annoying. The train tracks to place them onto the landscape can be the most annoying bit of the game, this also includes bus stops and tram linesAlso, the game can be very annoying with the transport AI. I built a massive train system and thankfully it worked very well and made a lot of income, however, when I requested a train to go into a depot, it completely went onto a different line and completely ruined the train service (just like the Tube) and everything stopped making the game compeltely unplayable...Another thing which bugged me was the level of difficulty. The game is not easy and you would end up bankrupt immediately if not selective. Of course I understand that the game has to have some challenge but you can fail instantly if you muck up somethingTrain Fever also gives you absolutely no tutorial, it just throws you into the game and makes you read a long boring tutorial... no. Also, when placing the train tracks especially, the game's framerate chugs like hell, so much so, I have to stop and wait for the game to regain the framerates to make it even playable. Also, the game freezed for a couple of seconds to autosave which can be annoyingHowever, the game does have a fantastic level amount of detail. From the trains, to the house, people and cars and landscape, this also includes the sound effects, especially the train sound effects. The music on the other hand, isn't that greatI knew that the developers wanted to make a very good Transport Tycoon game but did not manage completely but tried. Thankfully they gave away free DLC which takes place in USA and they are developing a sequel to Train Fever called Transport Fever which I have high hopes forTrain Fever is a mixed bag when it comes to purchasing, I am in the middle when it comes to recommending it or not. I highly suggest that for this game you check out some reviews and gameplay videos before considering purchasing, but overall, Train Fever isn't that bad!RECOMMENDED :)"
76561198043521169,Recommended,304730,29375143,Posted: 20 January,all,dmmarkow,My 7 year old son loves trains and loves this game - hours of sandbox entertainment.  Great graphics and fun to watch.
,Recommended,304730,11988764,"Posted: 5 September, 2014",all,Yavianice,"Great game with lots of potential (mods!). However, there are also some very weird, random, and obvious shortcomings (some are really really annoying) in this game, such as:- No real tutorial available, while the game has a steep learning curve.- No background sounds available, which is a big shortcoming!- No clear way to tell where people want to go to/work/leasure, which requires a lot of expensive trial and error. Use the Traffic Giant method by showing through colors where people work. Now only a 'Land Use' map is available, but it doesn't mean people actually work next door (why have a transportation simulator otherwise).- No minimap in the game, a big shortcoming with the huge maps.- When you have many lines, it becomes very hard to distinguish where lines are headed on different tracks, especially when you are colorblind. Would be better if you could highlight certain lines more clearly.- Very few vehicles available in the game, although modders are working to change that- You can construct railway crossings over roads, but not the other way around, which is SUPER ANNOYING- Only straight railway stations? Really??- Upgrading railway stations is incredibly annoying- Depots are one way only, which is terrible in case you have to replace a train in late game. Drive through depots are more realistic, and much better.- For some weird reasons,you cannot construct ""X"" crossovers for rails, only Y mergers, which is very annoying when you merge a lot of rails. ""X"" crossovers are part of elemental train track design, and leaving it out is completely random and not well thought out.- They should have made it easier to make flyovers. Making realistic flyovers is very hard due to the way the bridge pillars are implemented. Tunnels should be easier to make, too.- No way to customize the paint schemes of the trains. Devs say this is for reaslisms sake (while oddly not incorporating any realistic logos), however in real life, trains have been in different color schemes all the time in different decades (e.g. german trains) or special schemes. The trains are also a random collection of german/swiss/austrian trains, which makes the lack of paint schemes even more weird and unrealistic.It just seems to me that the devs didn't really think it through that much. However, despite these shortcomings, it is still a great game to play. Lets hope that the mods or devs will alleviate these weird shortcomings soon. Some pros:- It looks great- Trains are nice (especially steam trains!)- Runs smoothly for me so far (Retina Macbook Pro, with nVidia card, with Bootcamp), no crashes or bugs to speak of- Give it a few weeks/months when some mods have arrived, and it will be even more awesome."
