76561198019440106,Recommended,304730,21430304,"Posted: 24 February, 2016",all,coastertroy,"Very steep learning curve. Watch a few videos on YouTube if you get frustrated. Fun game though, especially if you get it on sale. Not worth $20, but anything under that it's a good buy.Some things I've learned: You don't need to add a bus line or tram line to a city before you connect passenger rail.Passenger rail is the most lucrative thing you can do (That I've found) - start early with one good line on flat land and you'll do well.Be very catutious before investing a lot of money in cargo lines, so far they've been money pits in 9/10 situations. Even when the cargo is really flowing I haven't had a lot of luck generating a lot of profit from it.Signals are unecessairly complicated but once you get it it makes sense.Have fun!"
